      <h2>Webinar</h2>
      <p>Many of our members are on the frontline facing challenges during this pandemic. We have been able to give them a voice and have a forum for them to share their views.</p>
      <p>Our virtual round table discussions have been unique because the participants were heroes on the frontline – what they said came from the bottom of their hearts.</p>

      <h3>Our recent discussions:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>End of life care in this pandemic led by Jeremy Johnson</li>
        <li>Challenges in maternity care led by Himansu Basu</li>
        <li>Covid testing facts and fiction led by Gabriele Mallapaty</li>
        <li>Skin manifestation of Covid-19 – led by John Strasswimmer</li>
        <li>Collaboration with Water and Sanitation Rotary Action Group – led by Ron Denham and John Philip</li>
        <li>Medical equipment – procurement and donation – sharing good practices and learning lessons.</li>
        <li>Covid-19 and medical ethics led by Dr Benjamin Stoff</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This is a voluntary group – we use this to disseminate general information about new information of interest. Members can use the group to exchange ideas.</p>

      <h3>Posting</h3>
      <p>Selected articles of interest are posted on this site.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/news/poliomyelitis-yesterday-today-and-tomorrow-almost-at-the-end-rotarys">Poliomyelitis: yesterday, today and tomorrow</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://ponseti.medicine.uiowa.edu/about-us/dr-ponseti" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The clubfoot treatment revolution: Dr. Ponseti</a></li>
      </ul>

